        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 11:47PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1146 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 23 miles northeast of Rankin, moving northeast at 60
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Saint Lawrence, Best, Garden City, and Stiles.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
